'''New Yorkers United for Marriage''' is an [[LGBT rights]] umbrella group in the US State of [[New York (state)|New York]], formed on April 20, 2011 in order to coordinate and organize the push for the legalization of same-sex marriage within the state. Participating groups in the coalition include [[Empire State Pride Agenda]], Marriage Equality New York, as well as the New York State chapters of [[Freedom to Marry]], [[Human Rights Campaign]], [[GLAAD]], the [[League of Women Voters]], and the [[Log Cabin Republicans]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lgbtqnation.com/2011/04/gay-rights-advocates-unite-efforts-to-legalize-same-sex-marriage-in-new-york/ |title=Gay rights advocates unite efforts to legalize same-sex marriage in New York – LGBTQ Nation |publisher=Lgbtqnation.com |date=2011-04-12 |accessdate=2013-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Bolcer |first=Julie |url=http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2011/04/21/Log_Cabin_to_Join_NY_Marriage_Coalition/ |title=Log Cabin to Join NY Marriage Coalition |publisher=Advocate.com |date=2011-04-21 |accessdate=2013-12-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Bolcer |first=Julie |url=http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2011/04/25/League_of_Women_Voters_in_NY_Marriage_Coalition/ |title=League of Women Voters in NY Marriage Coalition |publisher=Advocate.com |date=2011-04-25 |accessdate=2013-12-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504105722/http://www.advocate.com/News/Daily_News/2011/04/25/League_of_Women_Voters_in_NY_Marriage_Coalition/ |archivedate=2011-05-04 |df= }}</ref>

