'''Social Equality Justice day''' is a day recognizing the need to promote efforts to tackle issues such as [[poverty]], [[social exclusion|exclusion]] and [[unemployment]]. Many organizations, including the UN, American Library Association (ALA) [http://ala.org/advocacy/diversity], and the International Labour Office, make statements on the importance of social justice for people. Many organizations also present plans for greater social justice by tackling poverty, social and economic exclusion and unemployment. The [[United Nations General Assembly]] has decided to observe 20 February annually, approved on 26 November 2007 and starting in 2009, as the World Day of Social Justice.<ref>[https://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=24801 ''UN declares 20 February as World Day of Social Justice'']</ref>
The Declaration focuses on guaranteeing fair outcomes for all through employment, social protection, social dialogue, and fundamental principles and rights.
==Teaching Social Justice Day==
Topics ideal for teaching students including childhood poverty, global citizenship, human rights and sustainable development with a series of lessons available by country with the United Nations and other programs.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://teachers.theguardian.com/assets/united-nations-matters-lesson-plans-una-uk?CMP=edi_44|title=United Nations Matters lesson plans - by UNA-UK|date=2013-09-04|work=Guardian Teacher Network|access-date=2018-02-20|language=en}}</ref> Oxfam's food for thought power point which shows students the global food system that then has the opportunity for students to share their thoughts and experiences.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://teachers.theguardian.com/assets/power-shift-power-point-secondary-%E2%80%93-oxfam%E2%80%99s-food-thought-project|title=Power-shift power point (secondary) – Oxfam’s Food for Thought project|date=2011-12-23|website=Guardian Teacher Network|language=en|access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref> The lesson plans and collections available are for students of all ages.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/teacher-network/teacher-blog/2014/feb/17/how-to-teach-social-justice-resources-lesson-plans|title=How to teach … social justice|last=Hannah|first=Valerie|date=2014-02-17|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-02-20}}</ref>
